    "llm_gate_instruction": "INTERNAL GATE \u2014 output is never shown to the user. Gate 1: {gate_question}. You MUST output ONLY a JSON object and nothing else. Format: {\"gate\": \"<value>\"} where <value> is exactly one of: {category_options}. No-tool values \u2014 {no_tool_categories} \u2014 skip tools and go straight to synthesis. Tool values \u2014 {tool_bearing_categories} \u2014 open the tool menu. IMPORTANT: when you choose a no-tool gate value (respond_directly or equivalent), you MUST also include a \"final_answer\" field with the actual natural-language reply the user should see. Example for a direct conversational reply: {\"gate\": \"respond_directly\", \"final_answer\": \"Hey! What can I help you with?\"}. Example for a synthesis reply: {\"gate\": \"respond_directly\", \"final_answer\": \"Based on the results: ...\"}. Example for a web lookup (no final_answer needed): {\"gate\": \"web_research\"}. Do NOT write any other text outside the JSON object.",
    "llm_tool_request_instruction": "INTERNAL GATE — output is never shown to the user. Gate 2: Select one tool from the `{selected_category_label}` category. You MUST output ONLY a JSON object and nothing else. Format: {\"tool_family\": \"{selected_category_key}\", \"tool\": \"<tool_key>\", \"request_payload\": <payload_object>}. Choose exactly one tool_key from the available tools below, and fill request_payload to match that tool's request_format. Do NOT write any other text, explanation, or sentence — only the JSON object. Example: {\"tool_family\": \"{selected_category_key}\", \"tool\": \"web_search\", \"request_payload\": {\"source\": \"web\", \"query\": \"search terms here\", \"aperture\": \"medium\"}}.\n\nAvailable tools (JSON):\n{selected_tool_menu_json}",
